  "instructions": [
    "Heat 1 tablespoon of coconut oil in a large wok over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the garlic, galangal, and chili peppers. Cook until fragrant, about 2 minutes.",
    "Add the Chinese cabbage and cook until it starts to soften, about 3 minutes.",
    "Add the fish sauce, palm sugar, and salt. Stir to combine.",
    "Add the Thai basil and mint leaves. Stir-fry for another minute.",
    "Transfer the Nam Prik to a serving bowl and serve hot with lime wedges on the side.",
    "Serve with additional lime wedges for squeezing over the top.",
    "Adjust the seasoning as needed.",
    "Garnish with additional Thai basil and mint leaves if desired.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
